        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="bg-white border-l-[3px] border-red-600 p-6 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-black text-red-800 text-lg mb-2">Mistake #1: Outdated Tap List (Do This Instead)</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>77% of brewery websites have outdated tap lists.</strong> Showing beers from 2019, beers kicked weeks ago, or "coming soon" beers that never launched. Beer-seekers see outdated list ‚Üí assume closed or out of business ‚Üí skip brewery. Result: Lost traffic daily, poor Google ranking, frustrated customers calling "Is this list current?"</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Fix:</strong> Live tap list integration (TapRm, Untappd for Business, or manual daily updates). Automatic updates when kegs kick (integrates with POS). "Last updated: Today" timestamp. Current beers = available = visit taproom. Golden Grain increased taproom traffic 340% with live tap list. Outdated list = zero traffic. Live list = full taps.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-l-[3px] border-red-600 p-6 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-black text-red-800 text-lg mb-2">Mistake #2: No Food Pairings or Menu (Do This Instead)</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>68% of breweries don't show food pairings or menus.</strong> Beer-seekers want to know: "What should I eat with this IPA?" No food info = order beer, leave when hungry = lost food revenue. Result: Lower average ticket (beer only), shorter visits, missed food truck partnerships.</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Fix:</strong> Food pairing suggestions prominently ("IPA pairs with spicy tacos, aged cheddar, burgers"). Food menu if you have kitchen (or list food truck schedule). "Great with:" section on each beer page. Golden Grain increased average ticket 24% with food pairings (customers stay longer, order food when hungry). Food = beer companion = higher ticket = longer visits.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-l-[3px] border-red-600 p-6 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-black text-red-800 text-lg mb-2">Mistake #3: No Can Ordering or Hidden (Do This Instead)</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>64% of breweries don't offer can ordering or bury it in navigation.</strong> Beer-seeker wants beer but can't visit taproom (lives 2 hours away, busy schedule). No online ordering = lost sale. Result: Limited reach, taproom-only revenue, customers buy competitor cans at liquor store.</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Fix:</strong> Can ordering prominent on homepage ("Order Cans Online" button above fold). E-commerce integration (Shopify, Squarespace Commerce, BigCommerce). Local delivery option (same-day delivery in 20-mile radius). Shipping for out-of-area customers. Golden Grain increased can sales 187% with online ordering visible. Cans = taproom in a can = reach customers who can't visit taproom.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-l-[3px] border-red-600 p-6 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-black text-red-800 text-lg mb-2">Mistake #4: Buried Taproom Hours or Location (Do This Instead)</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>71% of breweries bury taproom hours in footer or contact page.</strong> Beer-seeker searches "brewery near me" ‚Üí finds website ‚Üí can't find hours or address ‚Üí gives up ‚Üí goes to competitor. Result: Lost walk-in traffic, frustrated customers, poor local SEO ranking.</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Fix:</strong> Taproom hours and address prominently on homepage (above fold). "Open Now" indicator (changes based on time of day). Google Maps integration (taproom location visible in search results). Directions button ("Get Directions" opens Google Maps). Mobile-optimized directions (73% check on phones). Make it impossible to miss when you're open and where you are.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-l-[3px] border-red-600 p-6 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-black text-red-800 text-lg mb-2">Mistake #5: No Brewing Story or Craft (Do This Instead)</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>59% of breweries don't tell their story.</strong> Beer-seekers love craft. Want to know: How do you brew? What ingredients? What's your philosophy? No story = generic brewery = no emotional connection. Result: Lower loyalty, fewer repeat customers, commodity pricing pressure.</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Fix:</strong> "Our Story" page (brewing journey, philosophy, process). Equipment photos (4-barrel system, fermenters, bottling line). Ingredient sourcing (local farms, NC grains, well water vs municipal). Behind-the-scenes content (brew day photos, recipe development). Golden Grain increased repeat customers 53% with brewing story. Story = craft = love brand = return customers who pay premium for quality.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-l-[3px] border-red-600 p-6 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-black text-red-800 text-lg mb-2">Mistake #6: Poor Mobile Tap List Experience (Do This Instead)</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>73% of beer-seekers check tap lists on phones.</strong> Brewery website not mobile-optimized: tiny text, unclickable buttons, horizontal scrolling, slow load. Result: 67% bounce rate, lost mobile traffic, customers skip to brewery with mobile-friendly site.</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Fix:</strong> Mobile-first tap list design (test on phone first). Large tap buttons (easy to tap). Swipe-to-browse (gesture for next beer). Fast load time (under 3 seconds). "Call for directions" button (one-tap). 73% of beer-seekers browse on phones. If your site doesn't work on mobile, you're losing 73% of potential taproom visitors. Beer = mobile. Breweries = mobile.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

