      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-yellow-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Should breweries sell cans online or focus on taproom?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Both. Taproom = experience, cans = reach.</strong> Taproom drives local loyalty, can sales extends brand beyond local. Need both for growth.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Platform strategy:</strong> Squarespace for taproom-focused (basic can sales via Ecwid or Commerce plans). Shopify for can-focused (full e-commerce with inventory sync). Webflow for brand-focused (multi-taproom, custom booking).</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Revenue reality:</strong> Golden Grain's can sales +187% after adding online ordering. Cans = taproom in a can = reach customers who can't visit taproom (2 hours away, busy schedule). Don't limit yourself to geography.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-yellow-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">What should breweries put on their website?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Minimum (required):</strong> Live current tap list (not outdated - integrate with TapRm or manual daily updates), beer descriptions (ABV, IBU, tasting notes), can ordering prominent, taproom hours/address, food menu or pairings, brewing story, upcoming events calendar, age verification (21+ gate required).</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Optional but powerful:</strong> Beer photography (beautiful taproom shots, beer pours), brewing process photos, team bios, merchandise store, loyalty program signup, local delivery information, private event booking, beer club membership.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Critical:</strong> Live tap list is non-negotiable. 77% of brewery websites have outdated lists. Golden Grain increased taproom traffic 340% with live current list. Outdated list = assume closed = lost traffic daily.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-yellow-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">How much does a brewery website cost?</h3>
